\pard\f0\fs28  Most plants from Krym differ from those from the Balkan peninsula in having almost flat leaf-margins. They have been treated as two different species on the basis of indumentum characters and of having ciliate ({\i T. pseudohumillimus}) or nonciliate ({\i T. tauricus}) upper calyx-teeth. The chromosome number cited refers to plants from Krym.
