\pard\f0\fs28  Sect. THYMUS (Sect.{\i  Vulgares} Velen., Sect.{\i  Zygis} Willk.). Small shrubs. Leaves with prominent mid-vein and usually revolute margins, usually tomentose at least beneath. Bracts similar to leaves or not, mostly greenish. Calyx more or less campanulate; upper teeth more or less as long as wide. Corolla scarcely longer to distinctly longer than calyx.
\par

