\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. T. capitellatus} Hoffmanns. & Link,{\i  Fl. Port. }{\b 1}: 125 (1809). 20-40 cm, with erect to patent woody branches bearing axillary leaf-clusters. Cauline leaves 3-5 × 1-1·5 mm, petiolate, narrowly ovate, tomentose; margins revolute, not ciliate. Inflorescence compound, of subglobose, often pedunculate cymes 6-8 mm in diameter. Bracts broadly ovate, greenish. Calyx 3-4 mm, campanulate; upper teeth about as long as wide, not ciliate. Corolla whitish. •{\i  S. Portugal.} Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. T. camphoratus} Hoffmanns. & Link,{\i  op. cit.} 131 (1809) ({\i T. algarbiensis} Lange). Like {\b 16} but inflorescence 10-18 mm in diameter, terminal; bracts often purplish; calyx 4-6 mm, the upper teeth triangular-subulate, usually ciliate. •{\i  S. Portugal.} Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 18. T. carnosus} Boiss.,{\i  Voy. Bot. Midi Esp.}{\b  2}: 490 (1841). Pulvinate, 20-40 cm, with erect to ascending woody branches bearing axillary leaf-clusters. Leaves 5-7 × 1-2 mm, petiolate, ovate-lanceolate, fleshy, glabrous above, tomentose beneath; margins revolute, ciliate at base. Inflorescence 1-3 cm. Bracts ovate, greenish. Calyx 3-4 mm, the tube campanulate; upper teeth as long as wide, not ciliate. Corolla whitish.{\i  Maritime sands. • S. Portugal.} Lu.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 19. T. vulgaris} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 591 (1753) (incl.{\i  T. aestivus} Reuter ex Willk.,{\i  T. ilerdensis} F. González ex Costa, {\i T. valentinus} Rouy,{\i  T. webbianus} Rouy). 10-30(-50) cm, with erect to semipatent woody branches. Leaves 3-8 × 0·5-2·5 mm, linear to elliptical, scarcely exceeding the axillary leaf-clusters, petiolate, tomentose; margins revolute, not ciliate. Inflorescence capituliform or interrupted, many-flowered. Bracts similar to the leaves but somewhat wider and sometimes with almost flat margins, greyish-green. Calyx 3-4 mm, shortly hairy, the tube campanulate; upper teeth as long as wide, not ciliate. Corolla whitish to pale purple. 2n = 30. •{\i  W. Mediterranean region, extending to S.E. Italy.} ?Co Ga Hs It [Bl He].
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   Very variable in shape of leaves, bracts and inflorescence. Widely cultivated as a pot-herb.
