\pard\f0\fs28 {\b   T. glandulosus} Lag. ex H. del Villar,{\i  Cavanillesia}{\b  6}: 105 (1934), non Req., from 2 or 3 localities in S.E. Spain (prov. Almeria), and also from N. Africa, seems not to be specifically different from {\b 20}. It has longer internodes, leaves 8-10 mm, and white to purplish-violet corolla. It is said to flower in spring (not in winter as {\b 20}).
