\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 21. T. zygis} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 591 (1753) (incl.{\i  T. sabulicola} Cosson, {\i T. sylvestris} Hoffmanns. & Link). 10-30 cm, with ascending to erect, puberulent, woody stems. Leaves 6-10 × 1 mm, usually exceeding the axillary leaf-clusters, linear, subacute, sessile, tomentose; margins revolute, sparsely ciliate at base. Inflorescence up to 10 cm, usually interrupted. Bracts similar to the leaves, mostly exceeding the verticillasters. Calyx 3-4 mm, shortly tomentose, greyish-green, the tube campanulate; upper teeth as long as wide, usually not ciliate. Corolla whitish. 2n = 60.{\i  Spain and Portugal.} Hs Lu.
